<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0598 </DOCNO><TEXT>In many administrative procedures the position of third parties is notyet clarified. The author discusses the Muelheim-Kaerlich decision ofthe Federal Constitutional Court and the importance of sec. 13, para.2 Administrative Procedure Act. The authority is obliged to ensure inthe administrative procedure the participation of citizens, whose rightscan be injured by the decision.</TEXT></DOC>